@ptn・8 We are now updating the challenge period, which will better reflect the scoring criteria for the main competition. The primary changes are:
* Removal of Sortino, in favor of MDD. MDD limit for challenge period is 2%, any drawdown beyond this will result in failure of the challenge period.
* Reduction of the returns requirement from 3.25% to 2.5%

@ptn・8 We have updated the MDD penalty and the Consistency penalties with a new update. Here is a high level summary of changes:
The max drawdown penalty will now use an expected value normalization by default, with slight penalties added after 1.5%MDD until 5%MDD. This means that a miner with MDD of 0.5 and returns of 1% is identical to a miner of MDD 1 and returns 2% in the system. There are also penalties below 0.25% MDD, to keep traders from tiny leverages. As such, the effective region with no penalties is between 0.25% MDD and 1.5%MDD - as long as your strategy is to stay within the MDD of your choosing within this range, there will be effectively no penalties for your miner. We are now also tracking MDD over a 30 day period instead of two weeks.

The consistency penalty is also slightly different. We recognize that with each trade period, the portfolio value of miners will change. If your portfolio value changes by more than 30x the typical portfolio value change over the period, you will start to receive severe consistency penalties. This has the same intuition as with the prior system, just a slight update to the hyperparameters and new focus on overall portfolio value.

We'll release specific details as we get a clearer idea of what the engineering implementation will look like for us.

@kabar we move pretty quickly, and want to give the community as much advance notice as we can about upcoming changes, particularly when we may implement that change just a few days later - sometimes things pop up in between. This was particularly the case as we were refining the scoring mechanism, but should be generally slowing down now. One of our priorities is to remove the challenge period, but we want to make sure it's done in a way that can still conserve the level of repeatable behavior we need for a proper output of the system, which we believe is the reorganization of funding rates / fees right now

